							<!-- End each blog post -->
							
														
							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/elizuzovsky/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/elizuzovsky-e1739568499165-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/elizuzovsky-e1739568499165-300x300.jpg 2x" alt="Eli Zuzovsky" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/elizuzovsky/">Eli Zuzovsky</a></h6>
										Eli Zuzovsky holds degrees from Harvard and Oxford, where he studied as a Rhodes Scholar. In 2022, he was selected for the <em>Forbes</em> Israel "30 Under 30" list and the London Library Emerging Writers Program, and he is the winner of the 2025 Einstein Fellowship. His films and plays have been shown at the New York Jewish Film Festival, Boston's Museum of Fine Arts, the American Repertory Theater, and the Edinburgh Festival Fringe, among others. He currently lives in London. <em>Mazeltov</em> is his first novel.																			</div>
								</div><br class="clear"/><br/>
